Wildflowers

Wildflowers sway  
In the gentle breeze,  
A tapestry of colors  
Etched against the green.  
They bloom where they choose,  
Unfettered and free,  
Teaching us that  
In life’s randomness,  
Beauty finds its way.


- Gabriel Okara
